description: Suzanne Chapin-Donalson describes growing up in a culturally diverse neighborhood in Chicago. She talks about working with disadvantaged populations in Nashville, Tennessee and Milwaukee, Wisconsin. She recalls working with dementia patients as her first introduction into psychiatric nursing. She describes moving on to an in-patient hospital unit, which she says was an incredible learning experience. She currently works at an outpatient community support program, where she enjoys the team-based approach and continuity of care.

description: Vicki Krenz explains that she worked in a factory for 11 years before shifting to nursing. She talks about first working as a CNA in a nursing home. She describes communicating with dementia patients; how she worked nights and kept up her schooling; and about becoming an LPN and then RN. She talks about her job at the V.A. and then as a private duty nurse in patients' homes before eventually moving to the county jail. She explains about the stress there and describes the work environment. She notes that mental health is central to all nursing.
